  "prompt": "From which institute should I learn post production and lightning, sound camera etc for my YouTube channel in Delhi?",
  "response": "There are several reputable institutes in Delhi where you can learn post production, lighting, sound, and camera techniques for your YouTube channel. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n1. **Film and Television Institute of India (FTII)** - Although based in Pune, FTII has workshops and extension courses in various cities, including Delhi. They offer comprehensive courses in film production.\n\n2. **National School of Drama (NSD)** - NSD offers various courses related to film and theater, including workshops that might touch on aspects of production, lighting, and sound.\n\n3. **Whistling Woods International (WWI)** - This institute has a branch in Delhi and provides programs in filmmaking that encompass post-production, sound design, and cinematography.\n\n4. **Apex Institute of Film and Television** - Located in Dwarka, this institute offers diploma courses in filmmaking that cover a wide range of topics, including editing, sound, and lighting.\n\n5. **International Institute of Film and Television (IIFT)** - IIFT offers various courses related to film production, editing, and cinematography. They have a comprehensive curriculum for aspiring filmmakers.\n\n6. **Zee Institute of Media Arts (ZIMA)** - ZIMA provides various courses in media arts, including filmmaking, editing, and sound design, which can be beneficial for creating content for a YouTube channel.\n\n7. **Delhi Film Institute** - This institute offers courses in film direction, cinematography, editing, and sound design, tailored for aspiring filmmakers at all levels.\n\n8. **MAAC (Maya Academy of Advanced Cinematics)** - MAAC offers courses in animation, VFX, and filmmaking that cover various areas, including post-production and sound.\n\nMake sure to check the specific courses offered, faculty experience, and student reviews before making a decision. It may also be beneficial to look for workshops or short-term courses that focus specifically on aspects relevant to YouTube content creation.",
